Exercise 1.3.Define a procedure that takes three numbers as arguments and returns the sum of the 
squares of the two larger numbers. 

(define (square x) (* x x))
(define (sum-of-squares x y) (+ (square x) (square y)))

(define (sum-of-the-squares-of-the-larger-two x y z)
		(cond ((= (min x y z) x) (sum-of-squares y z))
			  ((= (min x y z) y) (sum-of-squares x z))
			  ((= (min x y z) z) (sum-of-squares y z))))


(sum-of-the-squares-of-the-larger-two 1 2 3)
(sum-of-the-squares-of-the-larger-two 5 2 1)
(sum-of-the-squares-of-the-larger-two 2 2 3)

Result:
13
5
13

